cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.GT 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a general approach to knowledge transfer using neural networks. It also involves neuroevolution, which is a subfield of machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with agents adapting to new domains and improving their performance through selective activation of previously learned neural structures. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves neuroevolution, which is a combination of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves analyzing the performance of the approach in a stochastic version of the Arcade Learning Environment, which is a video game environment. 

Finally, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves analyzing the success of transfer based on a high-level characterization of game dynamics.
